=====Usage notes=====
*This word is an [[enclitic]] just like other [[particle]]s. It is classified as [[助動詞]] (jodōshi) in traditional Japanese grammar, because of its particle-like phonological behavior.
*This word cannot be used after an ''i''-adjective. An ''i''-adjective alone suffices to end a sentence or clause. For example, 「美しい。」 means "Is beautiful."
**Some conjugations of the word can, however: 「美しい'''[[です]]'''。」「美しい'''だろう'''。」
*Although だ cannot be used to introduce a relative clause ending in a ''na''-adjective or noun – "学生だアリス" is wrong – some of the conjugations of だ can: [[学生]]である[[アリス]] (Alice who is a student), 学生だったアリス (Alice who was a student), 学生じゃないアリス (Alice who is not a student), 学生じゃなかったアリス (Alice who was not a student). [[です]], which ends sentences instead of relative clauses, cannot be used here.

